<section id="pde-constrained-inverse-problems" class="slide level2">
<h2>PDE-constrained Inverse Problems</h2>
<div class="columns">
<div class="column" style="width:50%;">
<div class="callout callout-note callout-titled callout-style-default">
<div class="callout-body">
<div class="callout-title">
<div class="callout-icon-container">
<i class="callout-icon"></i>
</div>
<p><strong>Forward Problem</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="callout-content">
<p>Given <span class="math inline">\(\Omega\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{f(x) }\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{p_0}\)</span>, find <span class="math inline">\(\color{blue}{p(x)}\)</span> such that <span class="math display">\[
\begin{aligned}
- \nabla \!\cdot\! \big(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\color{black}{\nabla} \color{blue}{p(x)} \big)&amp;= \color{red}{f(x) }
&amp;&amp; x\in \Omega, \\
\color{blue}{p(x)} &amp;= \color{red}{p_0}
&amp;&amp;x\in \partial\Omega .
\end{aligned}
\]</span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="column" style="width:50%;">
<div class="callout callout-important callout-titled callout-style-default">
<div class="callout-body">
<div class="callout-title">
<div class="callout-icon-container">
<i class="callout-icon"></i>
</div>
<p><strong>Inverse Problem</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="callout-content">
<p>Given <span class="math inline">\(\color{blue}{p(x)}\)</span>, find <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{f(x) }\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{p_0}\)</span> such that <span class="math display">\[
\begin{aligned}
- \nabla \!\cdot\! \big(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\color{black}{\nabla} \color{blue}{p(x)} \big)&amp;= \color{red}{f(x) }
&amp;&amp; x\in \Omega, \\
\color{blue}{p(x)} &amp;= \color{red}{p_0}
&amp;&amp;x\in \partial\Omega .
\end{aligned}
\]</span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
<p><strong>Overarching Applications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><p>Calibration of PDE-based models e.g. <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\)</span>, may be partially known (cannot be measured directly) or subject to <span class="alert">uncertainty</span>.</p></li>
<li><p>Tomography</p>
<ul>
<li>inference of physical properties e.g.<span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\)</span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="section" class="slide level2 scrollable">
<h2></h2>
<h3 id="a-class-of-inverse-problems-parameter-identification">A class of Inverse Problems: Parameter Identification</h3>
<p>Aim: Infer unknown parameters in PDE(s) given measurements of the solution of the PDE(s).</p>
<p>Setting: <span class="math display">\[\text{Forward Problem (FP)}:
    \begin{cases}
    Model~Equations ~(MEs): &amp; \mathcal{M}(\alert{u},\advg{p})=0 \\
   Prediction~of~QoI: &amp; d=\mathcal{H}(\advg{p})
      \end{cases}
\]</span> Forward Map: <span class="math inline">\(\mathcal{F}:U\to D\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(d=\mathcal{F}(\alert{u})\)</span>, maps inputs (parameters) to outputs.</p>
<p>Inverse Problem (IP): Find <span class="math inline">\(\alert{u^{\dagger}}\)</span> (the truth) given of <span class="math inline">\(d^{\dagger}=\mathcal{F}(\alert{u^{\dagger}})\)</span>.\</p>
<p>Common (modelling) assumption: <span class="math display">\[
\begin{align*}
\adv{\text{measurements:}\quad d^{\eta}}&amp;=\overbrace{\mathcal{F}(\alert{u^{\dagger}})}^{d^{\dagger}}+\eta,\qquad \eta: \text{measurement noise}
\end{align*}
\]</span> Applications of this class of IPs: Calibration and tomographic imaging.</p>
</section>
<section id="standard-standard-approaches" class="slide level2">
<h2>Standard standard approaches</h2>
<p>Forward Map: <span class="math inline">\(\mathcal{F}:U\to D\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(d=\mathcal{F}(\alert{u})\)</span>, maps input to outputs.\</p>
<p>:</p>
<p><span class="math display">\[\text{Find a LS solution:} \quad u^{\eta}=\arg\min_{u\in U}~~\overbrace{ \left\lVert \adv{d^{\eta}}-\mathcal{F}(\alert{u})\right\rVert^2}^{data~misfit}+\overbrace{\alpha\left\lVert \alert{u}\right\rVert_{?}^2}^{regularisation}\]</span> </p>
<p><span class="math display">\[\text{Find the posterior:}\quad \mathbb{P}(\alert{u}\vert \adv{d^{\eta}})\propto \overbrace{\mathbb{P}(\alert{u})}^{prior}\overbrace{\mathbb{P}( \adv{d^{\eta}}\vert \alert{u})}^{likelihood}\]</span></p>
<span class="math inline">\(\alert{u}\)</span> is a function (i.e. high-dimensional).
<p> Incorporate possible discontinuities of <span class="math inline">\(\alert{u}\)</span>.</p>
</section>
<section id="mathematical-framework" class="slide level2 scrollable">
<h2>Mathematical Framework</h2>
<div class="callout callout-important callout-titled callout-style-default">
<div class="callout-body">
<div class="callout-title">
<div class="callout-icon-container">
<i class="callout-icon"></i>
</div>
<p><strong>Inverse Problem</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="callout-content">
<p><span class="alert"><strong>Given measurements</strong></span> of <span class="math inline">\(\color{blue}{p(x)}\)</span>, denoted by <span class="math inline">\(\color{blue}{d}\)</span>, find <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{f(x) }\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{p_0}\)</span> such that <span class="math display">\[
\begin{aligned}
- \nabla \!\cdot\! \big(\color{red}{\kappa(x)}\color{black}{\nabla} \color{blue}{p(x)} \big)&amp;= \color{red}{f(x) }
&amp;&amp; x\in \Omega, \\
\color{blue}{p(x)} &amp;= \color{red}{p_0}
&amp;&amp;x\in \partial\Omega .
\end{aligned}
\]</span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Forward Operator:</strong> <span class="math inline">\(\color{red}{u=(\kappa, f, p_0)}\color{black}{ \xrightarrow{\;\;\mathcal{G}\;\;}}\color{blue}{\big\{p(x_{i})\big\}_{i=1}^{M}}\)</span></p>
<p><span class="alert"><strong>Inverse Problem</strong> (Naive formulation):</span></p>
<p><span class="math display">\[
u^{*}=\operatorname*{arg\,min}_{u\in \mathcal{U}}\left\lVert d-\mathcal{G}(u)\right\rVert^2
\]</span></p>
<div class="columns">
<div class="column" style="width:70%;">
<ul>
<li>Ill-posedness
<ul>
<li>Lack of uniqueness</li>
<li>Lack of stability (small noise → large changes in solutions)</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div><div class="column" style="width:30%;">
<p><a href="Figs/cat.png" class="lightbox" data-gallery="quarto-lightbox-gallery-1"><img role="img" data-src="data:image/png;base64,"></a></p>
</div></div>
</section>
<section id="classical-approach" class="slide level2">
<h2>Classical approach</h2>
<h3 id="challenges">Challenges</h3>
<p><span class="math display">\[
u^{*}=\operatorname*{arg\,min}_{u\in \mathcal{U}}\left\lVert d-\mathcal{G}(u)\right\rVert^2 +\alpha \left\lVert u\right\rVert_{\mathcal{R}}^2
\]</span></p>
<div class="columns">
<div class="column" style="width:70%;">
<ul>
<li>Ill-posedness
<ul>
<li>Lack of uniqueness</li>
<li>Lack of stability (small noise → large changes in solutions)</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div><div class="column" style="width:30%;">
<p><a href="Figs/cat.png" class="lightbox" data-gallery="quarto-lightbox-gallery-2"><img role="img" data-src="data:image/png;base64,"></a></p>
</div></div>
</section>
<section id="main-approaches" class="slide level2">
<h2>Main approaches</h2>
<div class="columns">
<div class="column" style="width:50%;">
<p>Classical (deterministic approach)</p>
<p><span class="math display">\[
u^{*}=\operatorname*{arg\,min}_{u\in \mathcal{U}}\left\lVert d-\mathcal{G}(u)\right\rVert^2
\]</span></p>
</div><div class="column" style="width:50%;">
<p>Bayesian <span class="math display">\[
\mathbb{P}(u\vert d)\propto \mathbb{P}(u\vert d)\mathbb{P}(d\vert u)
\]</span></p>
</div></div>
